      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1784809557643,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3. How would the system handle running test cases?",
      "fontSize": 23.72622282608696,
      "fontFamily": 7,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3. How would the system handle running test cases?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.15
    },
    {
      "id": "OdliyRUvcZ5aRXKCgI4Og",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -193.2930908203125,
      "y": 6188.2265625,
      "width": 799.039306640625,
      "height": 40,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1296385274,
      "version": 104,
      "versionNonce": 1234059258,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1784809750945,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Store one set of test cases per problem in a language-independent format (e.g., JSON) instead of\nmaintaining separate test cases for Python, Java, JavaScript, etc.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Store one set of test cases per problem in a language-independent format (e.g., JSON) instead of maintaining separate test cases for Python, Java, JavaScript, etc.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "EF_DRVwTg3wWmS1FxPeUV",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -196.83259925842282,
      "y": 6248.47265625,
      "width": 765.6495735168456,
      "height": 81.74999999999999,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1I",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 140058534,
      "version": 197,
      "versionNonce": 1823657914,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1784809780899,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Serialize complex data structures (like binary trees, linked lists, graphs) into a standard\nformat. \n\nFor example, a binary tree can be represented as a level-order array:",
      "fontSize": 16.349999999999998,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Serialize complex data structures (like binary trees, linked lists, graphs) into a standard format. \n\nFor example, a binary tree can be represented as a level-order array:",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
